> I'm attempting to devise a cipher which uses cryptographically secure hash
> functions (key-dependant) as building blocks. I wonder if anyone can point
> me to some reference material on the design, security, and cryptanalytic
> results of ciphers based on hash functions...

see
	SIAM J Comput. Vol. 17 No. 2 1988, p373
	by Michael Luby and Charles Rackoff
	How to construct pseudorandom permutations from pseudorandom functions.
